      • binaryName

        public @ClassGetName java.lang.String binaryName()
        Obtains the binary name of the class.

        Note that the retrieved value may not adhere to the JDK binary name specification. The actual returned value is obtained from Class.getName(). In most cases, the Class.getName() and the JDK-spec binary name coincide.

        Returns:
        the name with the OUTER_CLASS_DELIMITERs between nested classed if any
        Implementation Requirements:
        This method returns the same value as does the value() method. Use this method for more clarity in the client code.

      • orBuilder

        public ClassName orBuilder()
        Obtains the name of the MessageOrBuilder interface for this message class.

        If this class name is com.acme.cms.Customer, the resulting class name would be com.acme.cms.CustomerOrBuilder.

        If this class name is dotted, then the resulting name is dotted.

        Returns:
        MessageOrBuilder interface FQN

      • toSimple

        public SimpleClassName toSimple()
        Converts fully-qualified name to simple name. If the class is nested inside one or more classes, the most nested name will be returned.

      • withoutPackage

        @Internal
public java.lang.String withoutPackage()
        Obtains this class name without the package qualifier.

        The result is always dotted.

        Returns:
        this name without the package

      • topLevelClass

        public SimpleClassName topLevelClass()
        Obtains the simple name of the top level class.

        If this class is top level, returns the simple name of this class. If this class is nested, returns the name of the declaring top level class.
